# Page Template: Detail Page

This template describes the structure, data flow, and component breakdown for a **detail (single-entity) page** in {{ display_name }}. Use it when building any page that shows a single resource fetched by ID.

---

## Purpose

A detail page displays the full representation of one entity. It allows the user to read all attributes, take actions (edit, delete, status change), and navigate to related entities. It must handle the not-found case gracefully.

---

## Data Flow

```
Browser requests /users/018e7b1a-...

Next.js Server Component
  └── calls getUser(id) from services/users.ts
        └── GET /api/users/018e7b1a-...
              └── Symfony returns User JSON
                    or 404 → Next.js renders notFound()

Server Component renders full page with user data
Browser receives HTML with data already present
```

The page ID comes from the URL segment (`params.id`). The Server Component fetches the resource and either renders it or calls `notFound()` from `next/navigation`.

---

## URL

```
/users/[id]
/products/[id]
/orders/[id]
```

Protected route. Each entity type has its own route segment. The `[id]` segment is a UUID.

